One solution to this would be to move the model.divBottom group from inside the main group that contains model.divLike and common, to outside it. I.e.:

\(
\( model.divTop | model.global \)\*,
\(
\(
\( \( \( model.divLike | model.divGenLike \), model.global\* \)+ \)
| \(
\( \( model.common \), model.global\* \)+,
\( \( model.divLike | model.divGenLike \), model.global\* \)\*
\)
\),
\)?,
\( \( model.divBottom \), model.global\* \)\*
\)
although I have not thought through and tested what other consequences there might be to this chagne. \(One obvious consequence is that
&lt;div&gt;&lt;trailer/&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
which is currently invalid would become valid. But since
