Version numbers:

Ubuntu: 9.04
tei-xsl: 5.24




Description:

This is a problem with the LaTeX stylesheet.  I'm attaching a zip file called paranote.zip, it contains files illustrating the problem:

Makefile      simple makefile to build a PDF out of the XML
myTEI.rnc     basic RNC created with Roma
paranote.xml  XML file giving examples of the problems reported here
schemas.xml   Keeps nXML happy by linking paranote.xml to myTEI.rnc.

People wanting to use the Makefile should edit the STYLE variable before running make.

The file paranote.xml shows 2 related problems:

1\. The first problem is with paragraphs inside of notes:

&lt;p&gt;&lt;note&gt;&lt;p&gt;note contents&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/note&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

is transformed into a footnote which begins with the \par command. LaTeX then produces a footnote which begins with a blank line.

2\. The second problem is with lines in line groups:

&lt;p&gt;
First example using quote... before lg...
&lt;quote&gt;
&lt;lg&gt;&lt;l&gt;line 1&lt;/l&gt;&lt;l&gt;line 2&lt;/l&gt;&lt;/lg&gt;
&lt;/quote&gt;
After lg...
&lt;/p&gt;

is transformed into a quote which ends with \\\\.  This line break causes unwanted space in the final document.

A related case is this one:

&lt;p&gt;
Second example using q... before lg...
&lt;quote&gt;
&lt;lg&gt;&lt;l&gt;line 1&lt;/l&gt;&lt;l&gt;line 2&lt;/l&gt;&lt;/lg&gt;
&lt;/quote&gt;
After lg...
&lt;/p&gt;

The last \leftline creates an unwanted space.



Solution:

The problems here stem for a general problem: some LaTeX commands which are used to separate presentational elements within a larger structure must not be generated at the start or end of that structure.  So to speak of the cases above:

1\. Paragraphs in a footnote should not generate \par if they are first in the footnote.

2\. Lines in a line group would not generate \\\ if they are last in the group.  I do not have a good solution for fixing the \leftline case.

