Sorry, David is quite right -- I don't know what I was thinking of :-\{ 

&lt;graphic&gt; is a member of model.phrase, &lt;figure&gt; a member of model.inter, and that's the distinction.  

If we want to make &lt;figure&gt; global, we'd remove all its other model class memberships, obviously

To expand on the relation between this bug and request 1900115:

One of the items included in that request is to allow figure within bibl, because a figure can actually, even though accidentally, occur within a bibl. I collected some evidence of related phenomena to ponder in this context. See: http://peterboot.nl/tei/figures-everywhere.pdf. What this shows is figures \(on new pages\) interrupting rs, quote, list and name. \(Of these four, quote is the only place where figure is allowed to occur\). This suggests that figures can indeed occur almost anywhere. That does not necessarily mean figure should be global. Another option would be to split the rs, quote, list or name \(yes, the quote too, because even though a figure can occur within a quote, this figure is not actually part of the quote\). That would be the preference of the orthodox, I suppose. On the other hand, we all, I believe, would unhesitatingly place the page breaks inside of these elements. And we already allow graphic there. I think this argues for accepting Syd’s proposal. 

Another item included in 1900115 is to allow a figure where it was allowed in P4: at the end of a div, after a subdivision, like this:
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;figure/&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
Syd’s proposal solves that problem as well. 
\(And in fact there are more places where P5 caused a similar problem: between divs and between list items\).

tickets.description:
== Description ==

When converting a &lt;ptr target="footnoteid"/&gt; where "footnoteid" refers to a footnote, the following code is executed:

&lt;xsl:template match="tei:note" mode="xref"&gt;
&lt;xsl:number level="any"/&gt;
&lt;/xsl:template&gt;

However, notes are generated using the standard LaTeX \footnote \(or \endnote\) facility.  It is therefore possible that LaTeX's idea of footnote numbering will differ from XSL's idea.  In trivially simple documents, LaTeX and the XSL fragment above will have the same numbering but in more complex documents, especially documents where &lt;note&gt; can be processed in a number of different ways, the numbers generated by \footnote and by the fragment above will diverge.

== Illustration ==

I am attaching a zip file named teibug4.zip.  It contains files illustrating the problem.  Use make to generate the ltx and pdf files.

The file test.xml contains several paragraphs and footnotes.  I've set one footnote to be an endnote.  This example is awkward \(nobody would use endnotes like this\) but it does illustrate the problem well enough: if a &lt;note&gt; element is not converted to a footnote, then the numbers generated by &lt;ptr&gt; are off.

In the resulting example, you will see in footnote four "See notes 2 and 3."  The number 3 should be 1 because it is a reference to the one &lt;note&gt; element which is actually an endnote.

== Hackish Workaround ==

This is an incomplete solution hacked together to allow me to move forward with my work.  It does not take care of the first cases in the &lt;xsl:choose&gt; test.  I've overridden two templates and use \ref and \label to get proper numbers in place.  Note that \ref ends up appearing inside a \hyperlink element but this does not seem to bother LaTeX.

&lt;xsl:template match="tei:note" mode="xref"&gt;
&lt;xsl:text&gt;\ref\{&lt;/xsl:text&gt;&lt;xsl:value-of select="@xml:id"/&gt;&lt;xsl:text&gt;\}&lt;/xsl:text&gt;
&lt;/xsl:template&gt;

&lt;xsl:template match="tei:note"&gt;
&lt;xsl:if test="@xml:id"&gt;
&lt;xsl:text&gt;\hypertarget\{&lt;/xsl:text&gt;
&lt;xsl:value-of select="@xml:id"/&gt;
&lt;xsl:text&gt;\}\{\}&lt;/xsl:text&gt;
&lt;/xsl:if&gt;
&lt;xsl:choose&gt;
&lt;xsl:when test="@place='inline' or ancestor::tei:bibl or ancestor::tei:biblStruct"&gt; 
&lt;xsl:text&gt;\(&lt;/xsl:text&gt;
&lt;xsl:apply-templates/&gt;
&lt;xsl:text&gt;\) &lt;/xsl:text&gt;
&lt;/xsl:when&gt;
&lt;xsl:when test="@place='end'"&gt;
&lt;xsl:text&gt;\endnote\{&lt;/xsl:text&gt;
&lt;xsl:apply-templates/&gt;
&lt;xsl:text&gt;\}&lt;/xsl:text&gt;
&lt;/xsl:when&gt;
&lt;xsl:when test="@target"&gt;
&lt;xsl:text&gt;\footnotetext\{&lt;/xsl:text&gt;
&lt;xsl:apply-templates/&gt;
&lt;xsl:text&gt;\}&lt;/xsl:text&gt;
&lt;/xsl:when&gt;
&lt;xsl:otherwise&gt;
&lt;xsl:text&gt;\footnote\{\label\{&lt;/xsl:text&gt;&lt;xsl:value-of select="@xml:id"/&gt;&lt;xsl:text&gt;\}&lt;/xsl:text&gt;
&lt;xsl:apply-templates/&gt;
&lt;xsl:text&gt;\}&lt;/xsl:text&gt;
&lt;/xsl:otherwise&gt;
&lt;/xsl:choose&gt;
&lt;/xsl:template&gt;

