I added an attribute to the div-element. This attribute now appeared in the list of attributes in Roma but nowhere else. It was not included in the resulting schema. So I took a look at the ODD-file generated at the same time as the schema \(I also tried to have a DTD made, the attribute was not there, either.\) , and I found the attribute markes as "change", not as "add":

&lt;elementSpec ident="div" module="textstructure" mode="change"&gt;
&lt;attList&gt;
&lt;attDef ident="name" mode="change"&gt;
&lt;desc&gt;For naming document parts&lt;/desc&gt;
&lt;/attDef&gt;
&lt;/attList&gt;
&lt;/elementSpec&gt;


I then edited the ODD-file so that this part instead looked like this:

&lt;elementSpec ident="div" module="textstructure" mode="change"&gt;
&lt;attList&gt;
&lt;attDef ident="name" mode="add"&gt;
&lt;desc&gt;For naming document parts&lt;/desc&gt;
&lt;/attDef&gt;
&lt;/attList&gt;
&lt;/elementSpec&gt;

And then I uploaded this to Roma and clicked the button for creating a schema, and it worked.

