&lt;div&lt;br/&gt;   xmlns:my="http://www.example.org/ns/nonTEI"&gt;
&lt;\!-- ... --&gt;
&lt;p n="12" topic="rabbits"&gt;Flopsy, Mopsy, Cottontail, and
Peter...&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

In my PDF version of TEI P5, this bit looks as follows \(and seems correct here\):

&lt;div
xmlns:my="http://www.example.org/ns/nonTEI"&gt;
&lt;\!-- ... --&gt;
&lt;p n="12"   my:topic="rabbits"&gt;Flopsy, Mopsy, Cottontail, and
Peter...&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

Content model for &lt;category&gt; should be changed from:

element category
\{
att.global.attributes,
\( \( catDesc | model.glossLike\* \), category\* \)
\}

to:

element category
\{
att.global.attributes,
\( \( catDesc+ | model.glossLike\* \), category\* \)
\}

in order to allow for category descriptions in multiple languages, as in the following example from the National Corpus of Polish:

