The third issue with ePub generation is the title page, where the cover is.

The image is actually huge for a 6-inch ereader \(which is the standard for an eink ereader, not a tablet\).

I also wonder why a image is used instead of implementing it in code.

I think that something like this \(borrowed from the titlepage.html\) could do the job:

&lt;?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?&gt;
&lt;html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en"&gt;
&lt;head&gt;
&lt;meta name="author" content="Basil L. Gildersleeve"/&gt;
&lt;meta name="generator" content="Text Encoding Initiative Consortium XSLT stylesheets"/&gt;
&lt;meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8"/&gt;
&lt;meta name="DC.Title" content="Title page"/&gt;
&lt;meta name="DC.Type" content="Text"/&gt;
&lt;meta name="DC.Format" content="text/html"/&gt;
&lt;meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8"/&gt;
&lt;meta name="calibre:cover" content="true"/&gt;
&lt;title&gt;Title page&lt;/title&gt;
&lt;style type="text/css" title="override\_css"&gt;
@page \{padding: 0pt; margin:0pt\}
.titlepage \{ text-align: center; padding:0pt; margin: 0pt; font-size: 225% ; font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\}
p.covertitle \{ font-weight: bold; color: \#FFFFFF ; background-color: \#012148; margin: 5%; padding: 5%\}
p.covertitle \{margin: 10%\}
&lt;/style&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
&lt;div class="titlepage"&gt;
&lt;p class="covertitle"&gt;The Title&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="coverauthor"&gt;The Author&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

By the way, I think that the &lt;head&gt;&lt;title&gt;&lt;/title&gt;&lt;/head&gt; should contain the book title, that "&lt;meta name="calibre:cover" content="true"/&gt;" makes no sense here \(or am I missing something?\).

Many thanks for your help,


Pablo

